When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

    When multiple people are working on a project it would be beneficial to use a remote 
    repository so multiple people can access it from diferent locations.

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

    When you start working on a local repository and it has automatically pulled the changes,
    there could be changes you don't know about that interfere with the new code you are adding.

